-- int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to find one approved return per item
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_category_return_rates.sql
```sql
-- Calculate aggregated product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.quantity,
        c.category_name,
        r.return_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    COALESCE(category_name, '(unknown)') AS category_name,
    SUM(quantity) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(CASE
        WHEN return_id IS NOT NULL THEN quantity
        ELSE 0
    END) AS total_items_returned,
    SUM(CASE
        WHEN return_id IS NOT NULL THEN quantity
        ELSE 0
    END) * 1.0 / SUM(quantity) AS return_rate
FROM source
GROUP BY COALESCE(category_name, '(unknown)')
